{"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/recordscalendarui"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Reusable SwiftUI calendar records UI for apps that own their own data, persistence, and navigation."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarUI"},{"type":"text","text":" provides presentation-only calendar components for record-based apps. Host apps pass records, display configuration, selection state, and callbacks while keeping storage and detail navigation outside the package."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this package when you need a reusable week\/month calendar with a selected-day list and swipe-to-delete behavior, but each app needs different record values, text formatting, and detail screens."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Week scope uses the display calendar’s locale and first weekday to create a localized year, month, and week-of-month header. A Korean calendar displays a title such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2026년 7월 1주차"},{"type":"text","text":" without host formatting, and the week number follows the visible calendar grid."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in week-title localizations cover English, Simplified Chinese, Traditional Chinese, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese (Portugal), and Spanish. Other locales fall back to English."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.rowHeight"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the minimum selected-day row card height. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.rowSpacing"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the vertical spacing between selected-day rows, defaults to 5 points, can be customized by host apps, and clamps negative values to zero. Values below "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration<YourRecord>.minimumRowHeight"},{"type":"text","text":", currently 44 points, are clamped so row content keeps a standard touch target. Row spacing does not reduce the configured row height. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration<YourRecord>.minimumRowHeight(forRowSpacing:)"},{"type":"text","text":" remains as a deprecated compatibility helper; use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"minimumRowHeight"},{"type":"text","text":" for new code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.theme"},{"type":"text","text":" accepts semantic colors through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarTheme"},{"type":"text","text":", including the full-page background, calendar and record container background, primary and secondary page content colors, optional container-only primary and secondary content colors, and independent light and dark summary tile backgrounds. The default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".standard"},{"type":"text","text":" theme preserves the system grouped page background, material calendar container, grouped record containers, and existing green appearance. Host apps can supply adaptive SwiftUI colors without changing package internals."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Theme initialization without an explicit light-mode secondary content color remains supported and derives that color from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"contentColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To change only surfaces, copy "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".standard"},{"type":"text","text":" and set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"backgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerBackgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":". The package applies the container color consistently to the calendar, selected-day empty state, and record rows. Set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerContentColor"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerSecondaryContentColor"},{"type":"text","text":" when those containers need a foreground palette that differs from the page. Selected calendar days continue to use the page primary content color so it remains paired with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectedDayBackgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calendar day buttons can receive an accessibility label and value from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". The package passes a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarDayAccessibilityContext"},{"type":"text","text":" with the date, its display calendar, and the today, selected, and has-records states so host apps can provide their own localized full-date label and state text. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context.calendar"},{"type":"text","text":" when formatting the date so its locale and time zone stay consistent with the visible calendar. When these closures are omitted, the package preserves SwiftUI’s default day-number announcement. Selected dates also use the system selected accessibility trait."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"collection","externalID":"RecordsCalendarUI","modules":[{"name":"RecordsCalendarUI"}],"roleHeading":"Framework","symbolKind":"module","title":"RecordsCalendarUI"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Calendar Presentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarView","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarConfiguration","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarWeekTitleContext","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarTheme","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarDisplayScope"],"anchor":"Calendar-Presentation"},{"title":"Record Model Boundary","identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarEntry"],"anchor":"Record-Model-Boundary"},{"generated":true,"title":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarDayAccessibilityContext"],"anchor":"Structures"}],"references":{"doc://recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI/documentation/RecordsCalendarUI/RecordsCalendarConfiguration":{"title":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarConfiguration","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/recordscalendarui\/recordscalendarconfiguration","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI/documentation/RecordsCalendarUI/RecordsCalendarTheme":{"title":"RecordsCalendarTheme","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarTheme","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RecordsCalendarTheme","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/recordscalendarui\/recordscalendartheme","n